label: accuracy
definition: experimental degree of eror

label: alteration degree
definition: Free text describing the degree of alteration or metamorphic phase that has affected a rock. [This element may need to be split into hydrothermal mineralogical change and metamorphic phases]

label: alteration type
definition: Free text describing the type of change that has taken place
examples: chloritisation, migmatisation, cataclastic brecciation etc.

label: analysis by
definition: Persons or organisations carrying out the analysis

label: analysis date time
definition: When the analysis was carried out

label: analysis method
definition: Analytical method used
examples: x-ray diffraction, electron probe, chemical analysis or thin section.

label: analysis reference
definition: Individual documentary reference linked to an analysis. Uses abcd:Reference Type

label: analysis references
definition: Container for 1 or more references related to the analysis

label: analysis result
definition: Individual measurement made during an analysis
examples: the chemical composition of a mineral

label: analysis result comment
definition: Free text comment relating to the analysis results

label: analysis results
definition: Container for multiple values obtained by analysis
examples: percentages of different elements present

label: analysis text
definition: Free text to describe the analysis. This may be of value, for instance, if the mineral has been confirmed by x-ray diffraction but no actual analysis data are given in the analytical results.

label: applies to
definition: Used to qualify the measurement parameter

label: articulation
definition: Free text description of the articulation in the preserved specimen - applies to invertebrate shells and exoskeletons as well as vertebrate skeletons.
examples: articulated, dis-articulated, single valves etc.

label: assemblage origin
definition: Free text description relating to the mode of origin of the assemblage
examples: unknown, allocthonous, autocthonous, paraautocthonous etc.

label: associated fossil assemblage
definition: Container element for describing fossil assemblage associated with the rock or mineral unit

label: associated fossil assemblage text
definition: Free text for describing the occurrence, form or other features associated with this fossil assemblage
examples: fore-reef community, condensed reworked assemblage, serpulid bioherm with high concentration of gastropods etc.

label: associated fossil comment
definition: Free text for describing occurrence of this particular taxon or any of its features.

label: associated fossil list
definition: Container for one or more fossil taxa (including ichnotaxa) that constitute the fossil assemblage associated with the unit being described. Note that highly detailed information on identification or description of the taxa in the assemblage should be treated as separate but related units.

label: associated fossil name
definition: A single taxon name at any level
examples: trilobite or Dalmanites myops

label: associated mineral assemblage text
definition: Free text for describing the features or characteristics of the overall mineral assemblage
examples: typical North Yorkshire primary copper-rich sulphide assemblage with complex secondary alteration products

label: associated mineral comment
definition: Free text for describing the occurrence of this particular mineral or any of its features.

label: associated mineral list
definition: A single mineral name at any level of accuracy
examples: feldspar, pyroxene etc. or orthoclase, olivine, horneblende etc.

label: associated mineral name
definition: A single mineral name at any level of accuracy
examples: feldspar, pyroxene etc. or orthoclase, olivine, horneblende etc.

label: author team and year
definition: who named the mineral or rock and when

label: baseline datum
definition: Text - what is the baseline
examples: top of borehole or base of measured section

label: bed
definition: The smallest division of a named stratified series normally with well defined division from adjacent deposits.

label: bioerosion
definition: Free text description of damage due to biological action, such as, boring worms and sponges.

label: biostratigraphic attribution
definition: A single declaration of a fossil zone or subzone.

label: biostratigraphic attributions
definition: Container for optional multiple references to fossil zones
examples: where a range of zones and subzones might be represented.

label: borehole
definition: Container for details specific to boreholes and wells. Does not contain spatial reference as this and details of platform etc. are under Gathering in main ABCD schema - but they could be copied to make an independent schema.

label: bottom surface
definition: Container for details of bottom surface of layer or stratum

label: bottom surface feature
definition: Text describing features at the base of a layer or stratum

label: certainty
definition: Degree of certainty associated with the date determination
examples: unknown, certain, uncertain, possibly, known wrong.

label: chrono stratigraphic division
definition: Classification level for the term
examples: eon, system, stage etc.

label: chronostratigraphic attribution
definition: A single declaration of an identifed chronostratigraphic date

label: chronostratigraphic attributions
definition: Allows for multiple and range declarations of chronostratigraphic terms. This element combines both chronostratigraphic and geochronologic terms with preference for chronostratigraphic. (Zalasiewicz et al. 2004)

label: chronostratigraphic name
definition: The formal  geo/chrono chronologic name
examples: Jurassic, Kimmeridgian etc.

label: classified name
definition: The formal name for the rock or mineral according to a given classification scheme

label: commissioned by
definition: Company or organisation who commissioned the borehole or well

label: completeness
definition: Free text descrbing the degree of completeness of the specimen
examples: complete, cephalon only, but may describe completeness of a part

label: contractor
definition: The drilling contractor who carried out the work

label: crystal form
definition: Container element for describing the crystal form of a mineral unit.

label: crystal form text
definition: Free text description of crystal form

label: crystal measurement
definition: Individual measurement or fact related to a crystal unit - container for standard MeasurementOrFact complex type from main schema

label: crystal measurements
definition: container for measurements of crystal physical and chemical characteristics

label: date text
definition: Free text to allow for vague dates or description of analysis period.

label: dating accuracy
definition: The degree of certainty or likely accuracy of the dating analysis

label: dating comment
definition: Free text description of the anlysis or its result.

label: dating qualifier
definition: Allows for qualification of date terms
examples: early/lower, middle, late/upper

label: depositional environment
definition: Container for describing the original environment in which thr rock was deposited or the mineral formed
examples: hypersaline lagoon, lacustrine, intertidal etc.

label: depositional environment text
definition: free text describing the original environment in which thr rock was deposited or the mineral formed
examples: hypersaline lagoon, lacustrine, intertidal etc.

label: depositional environment type
definition: keywords from enumerated list for indexing of depositional environments

label: diagenetic change
definition: Free text for describing any physical and chemical changes that took place in a sediment during the lithification process
examples: compaction, cementation, recrystallisation, dolomitisation and replacement.

label: dip degrees
definition: The dip in degrees of laminae or stratal surfaces in this layer

label: distance from baseline
definition: Number representing distance measured

label: drill method
definition: How the borehole or well was drilled
examples: reverse circulation drilling, diamond coring, percussion drilling, auger drilling, rotary/barber drilling etc.

label: earliest date
definition: The earliest date in a date range suggested by the analysis or the single date if only one is given

label: encrustation
definition: Free text description of biological encrustations, such as oysters and tube worms.

label: exact date
definition: Uses DateTime element from ABCD

label: feeding predation traces
definition: Free text description relating to aspects of feeding and predation
examples: ammonite with bite mark from plesiosaur,  shell drilled by predatory gastropod etc.

label: formation
definition: The primary lithostratigraphic unit characterised by its lithologic features although it may be diachronous.

label: fossil subzone name
definition: The subzone name, if any, this should ideally be in expanded form rather than abbreviated.

label: fossil zone name
definition: The actual name of the biozone. Ideally this should be in its expanded form although common usage tends to abbreviate the generic epithet.

label: full scientific name string
definition: Full formal name string as used in 'Taxon Identified' in main schema

label: geologists
definition: The geologist(s) and or organisation responsible for logging the borehole and or maintaining the borehole record.

label: group
definition: Lithostratigraphic unit consisting of two or more formations

label: hazard
definition: Container for describing hazards that may be associated with the specimen
examples: radioactive, toxic, carcinogens etc.

label: hazard text
definition: Free text describing any hazards that may be associated with the specimen/unit
examples: is it radioactive, poisonous, carcinogenic?

label: hole diameter
definition: Diameter of the borehole in milliimetres

label: hole direction
definition: Direction and inclination of the borehole or well

label: host rock stratigraphy
definition: Container for any stratigraphic determination specific to the host rock. For instance the gathering site may include a range of stratigraphic horizons whilst the unit host rock may represent just one. The unit itself might be different if it is allocthonous in origin. Minerals may be of a different age from their host rock.

label: host rock text
definition: Free text element for general description of host rock

label: identification analysis
definition: container for analytical techniques employed for identifying a mineral or rock. Note that this differs from the existing Measurement element in that it allows for multiple values to be obtained from a single analysis
examples: percentage values of elements in a mineral.

label: identification qualifier
definition: Element as used in TaxonIdentified

label: informal lithostratigraphic name
definition: An informal lithostratigraphic name (ie. one not yet characterised as a formation or member or an old name still in general use
examples: Schaumkalk as part of the Muschelkalk or Keuper Marl as a synonym of the Mercia Mudstone Group. includes language as an attribute.

label: informal name string
definition: Common name or language variant of formal mineral or rock name
examples: Fluor Spar.  Includes attribute for language.

label: isotope stratigraphic detail
definition: Free text describing the isotope correlation result.

label: isotope stratigraphic determination
definition: Single record of an isotope stratigraphic determination

label: isotope stratigraphic determinations
definition: Container for detail referring to any isotope concentration study. Isotope stratigraphy uses a range of readings over a sequence of rocks to create profiles that are correlated with dated sequences.

label: isotopes measured
definition: What isotopes were used for this correlation
examples: Oxygen, Strontium, Carbon or more specific (O18/O16)

label: latest date
definition: The latest date where a range of values is given

label: lithification host rock
definition: The degree of lithification of the host rock
examples: unlithified, poorly lthified, lithified etc.

label: lithology attributes host rock
definition: Lithological  description of host rock
examples: cross-bedded,  finely laminated etc. could use an enumeration or lookup list

label: lithology host rock
definition: The type of rock representing the host rock
examples: sandstone, mudstone, limestone etc

label: lithostratigraphic attribution
definition: An individual identification of a named lithostratigraphic unit
examples: The Hotwells Limestone Group.  The higher lithostratigraphic terms are also allowed to cover the possibility of rock name homonyms and indexing in the absence of  a complete dictionary of rock names.

label: lithostratigraphic attributions
definition: Allows for multiple identifications of any named lithostratigraphic units (
examples: Penarth Group, Langport Member, Rhaetic Bone Bed)

label: lower value
definition: Lower value of a range or single value. This can be expressed as a measured value
examples: 45% or as a chemical formula

label: magnetostratigraphic detail
definition: Free text describing the use of magnetostratigraphic correlation.

label: magnetostratigraphic determination
definition: Single record of magnetostratigraphic dating

label: magnetostratigraphic determinations
definition: Container for details of any magnetostratigraphic evidence cited to support the dating of rocks. Magnetostratigraphy uses a range of readings over a sequence of rocks to provide a pattern that is correlated with known dated sequences. It includes its own series of divisions including superchrons, chrons and subchrons.

label: material dated
definition: What was actually dated?
examples: Glauconite grains in a sandstone, wood from peat-core etc.

label: measure from baseline
definition: Container for recording eith the distance (in metres) from a fixed baseline
examples: top of a borehole or bottom of a measured section

label: measurement unit
definition: Units that DistanceFromBaseline are measured in
examples: metres

label: member
definition: A sub-division of a formation which may be local in extent or exhibits a distinctive lithology

label: mineral colour
definition: Description of coloration of the mineral

label: mineral description text
definition: Free text description of mineral unit which may include observations on its form and occurrence, origin or other associated facts

label: mineral habit
definition: Free text description of the mineral habit. Minerals occur in a variety of forms, which mayor may not be directly dependent on their crystalline structure
examples: nodular, columnar, radiating, mamillated, botryoidal, granular etc.

label: mineral measurement or fact
definition: Container for a single physical measurement or fact related to mineral

label: mineral measurements or facts
definition: Container for measurements or facts related to physical properties of mineral
examples: streak, cleavage, specific gravity etc.

label: mineral rock classification
definition: Classification to which the group name belongs
examples: Dana, Strunz etc.

label: mineral rock classification
definition: The classification from which this mineral or rockname has been taken

label: mineral rock group
definition: Equivalent to higher taxon for plants and animals. Container for multiple higher groupings for minerals (
examples: silicates, inosilicates) and rocks (

label: mineral rock group name
definition: A single instance of a higher 'taxon' for minerals
examples: Silicates or for rocks

label: mineral rock name atomised
definition: Container for formal name elements for rocks, minerals and meteorites

label: mode of transport
definition: How the material was transported
examples: glacier, turbidity current, meteorite etc.

label: name addendum
definition: element from TaxonIdentified complex type

label: name comments
definition: Free text relating to the identification of the mineral or rock

label: named geological feature
definition: The name for a geologic feature that is not a placename
examples: 'The Great Whin Sill', 'Bodmin Granite' or 'The Great Glen Fault'. Many landscape scale geologic and geomorphic features have names.

label: number of core boxes
definition: How many core boxes were collected from the borehole or well - integer

label: number of sub units
definition: Where the described sectionunit or  'layer' is represented by more than one similar unit
examples: a sequence of thin limestone beds with shale intercalations recorded as a single unit (layer)

label: organisation
definition: Organisation type from the abcd schema

label: orientation
definition: Free text description of the orientation of the fossil remains in the host rock
examples: unknown, life position, toppled etc.

label: original biominerals
definition: List of original organcis or biomaterial preserved in the specimen

label: original stratigraphy
definition: The original stratigraphic associations of allocthonous material
examples: a Devonian erratic obtained from a Pleistocene tillite.

label: overburden thickness
definition: Thickness in metres of non-logged over-burden before solid or logged material was reached.

label: parameter
definition: What the given value refers to
examples: amount of an individual element present in a crystalline structure or it could be chemical formula

label: part of organism
definition: Free text description relating to the part or parts of the organism that have been preserved
examples: shell, skeleton, skull, soft tissue etc.

label: perological analysis comment
definition: Free text element describing a petrological analysis or its results

label: person
definition: Person type from the abcd schema

label: petrological analysis
definition: Container for a single analysis related to the petrogenesis of a rock unit

label: petrologicalanalyses
definition: Container element for one or morre sets of analytical results relating to the petrogenesis of a rock unit.

label: petrology
definition: Container for petrographic descriptions related to a rock or mineral unit

label: petrology descriptive text
definition: Free text element for petrographic description of the associated rock or mineral unit.

label: place of origin
definition: The place of origin for material that has been transported during its history
examples: glacial erratics and meteorites

label: polarity chron
definition: Reference to numerical scheme for labelling time divisions based on magnetic anomalies and reversals

label: polarity subchron
definition: Any named subdivision of a Polarity Chron

label: polarity superchron
definition: largest division of magnetostratigraphic terms

label: position in sequence
definition: The position this stratigraphic 'unit' has in the sequence for the site.
examples: a bed number

label: post burial transportation
definition: Free text relating to any post burial transport of fossil material
examples: river transport, scree slope etc.

label: preservation alteration
definition: Container for description of preservation and alsteration of specimen

label: preservation alteration text
definition: Free text relating to mineralogical changes in preserved specimens
examples: original shell material preserved, replacement minerals, re-crystallisation, silicification etc.

label: preservation mode
definition: Container for preservation mode description and keywords

label: preservation mode keywords
definition: keywords for how fossil material has been preserved
examples: body, cast, mold, trace fossil, soft parts mineralised etc.

label: preservation mode text
definition: Free text for describing the mode of preservation
examples: is the specimen a cast or mold,are soft parts preserved or mineralised etc.

label: preservation quality
definition: Free text describing the preservation quality
examples: poor, medium, good, excellent. Includes preservation of anatomical detail and softparts.

label: preservation special mode
definition: Keyword for any special mode of preservation
examples: preserved in amber or frozen in tundra, tar pit etc.

label: pseudomorph
definition: Free text to describe any pseudomorph features associated with a mineral or rock unit. Types include substitution, encrustation and infill

label: radiometric date
definition: Container for a single radiometric date analysis

label: radiometric dates
definition: Container for absolute dates obtained from radiometric analysis.

label: radiometric dating method
definition: Method, analysis technique used to determine date
examples: radiocarbon, Potassium-Argon etc.

label: range position
definition: text field to mark if this date is the earlest in a possible range, midway or the latest. May need to be used if there is a possibility of a range of dates.

label: range position
definition: Range position if this attribution is the earliest, midway or latest in a possible range.
examples: It is not always clear what zone a particular taxon belongs to and therefore a range may be needed.

label: relationship to overlying layer
definition: Free text to record any observed relationship with overlying layer
examples: groove casts infilled by overlying sediment.

label: relationship to underlying layer
definition: Free text to describe relationship to underlying strata/layer
examples: unconformable and cross cuts strata or base of bed includes clasts of underlying sediment

label: replacement minerals
definition: List of replacement minerals in the specimen
examples: silica

label: rock mineral usage
definition: Description of the use to which this mineral or rock has been put
examples: building stone, ore, sculpture, cut gemstone.

label: rock physical characteristics
definition: Container for descriptive terms and measurements related to rocks
examples: grain size, grain sphericity, crystal sizes and orientations, laminations etc.

label: rock type
definition: For simple classification
examples: igneous, metamorphic, sedimentary or meteorite - enumeration list is provisional!

label: rock unit
definition: Container element for attributes restricted to rocks

label: sample g u i d
definition: A unique identifier for another Unit Record in ABCD

label: sample ref
definition: Identifier for this sample
examples: field log sample number, registration number or similar

label: sample text
definition: Short description of sample  - longer descriptions should be treated under separate unit records.

label: sample type
definition: What sort of sample this is. Could be an enumerated list

label: scientific name string
definition: Equivalent of Scientific Name but minerals and rocks do not use binomials
examples: Quartz, Fluorite etc.

label: section i d number
definition: Unique identifying code or number for this section, borehole or well

label: section log
definition: Container for the layer by layer description of the section, borehole or well. The layers or subdivisions are referred as SectionUnits - these represent layers, strata, beds, ore bodies, intrusive bodies etc. that might be recorded in a section or borehole. A SectionUnit or layer is also regarded as that which is recorded as a coherent sub-unit of the whole section or borehole. It may therefore be a single bed, a series of beds with similar characteristics or an unlayered body such as an igneous intrusion.

label: section name
definition: The name for the section
examples: Vallis Vale, Hapsford Bridge Section or it could be a borehole unique name. This may be different from the locality name.

label: section unit datum
definition: Text for where the measurement is taken
examples: top of bed or bottom of bed.

label: section unit descriptive text
definition: Free text description of the layer, stratum or rock body

label: section unit image
definition: Placeholder for multimedia complex type from main ABCD schema

label: section unit images
definition: Container for images related to this bed, layer or body within the measured section or borehole.

label: section unit number
definition: Either a numerical identifier used for sorting the sequence or a UnitFieldNumber. A sectionunit could be a bed, a layer, an intrusive body or anything else encountered in a section or borehole.

label: section unit sample
definition: Container for a single sample taken from this layer

label: section unit samples
definition: Container for samples taken from this layer. This should just list ABCD unit GUIDs to detailed unit/sample records but could be extended to use global types to create a standalone schema

label: sequence stratigraphic setting
definition: Keyword for position in sequence stratigraphy setting. Enumerated list.

label: shock metamorphic grade
definition: Free text for describing the type of alteration caused by impact, as in meteorites. Also called shock stage.

label: site sections
definition: Measured section or borehole record associated with the gathering site.

label: site stratigraphic attributions
definition: Individual stratigraphic determinations related to the Gathering site - not measured sections.

label: stratigraphic comment
definition: Free text comments relating to the straigraphy

label: stratigraphic date comment
definition: Free text element to allow discussion of geological age of a specimen or observed feature

label: stratigraphic measurement or fact
definition: Container for single instance of complex type MeasurementOrFact

label: stratigraphic measurements or facts
definition: Container element for multiple measurements (
examples: thickness, dip etc.) or facts (

label: stratigraphic reference
definition: Complex type for individual reference pertaining to stratigraphy uses abcd:Reference type

label: stratigraphic reference
definition: Details of individual documentary references to the straigraphy

label: stratigraphic references
definition: Container for any documentary references relating to the stratigraphy

label: stratigraphic references
definition: Container for complex type Reference. There may be more than one reference describing the stratigraphy.

label: stratigraphic section image
definition: This is a placeholder for MultiMedia complex type from the main ABCD schema

label: stratigraphic section images
definition: Container for images of the stratigraphic section or borehole and related media.

label: stratigraphy comment
definition: Free text for describing the stratigraphic context, correlation or similar notes

label: strike
definition: Direction of strike measured on stratal surface

label: supergroup
definition: Highest level of lithostratigraphic classification

label: tectonic setting
definition: Free text description of the relationship of the observed stratigraphy to its tectonic context
examples: sequence stratigraphy related to basin development and eustatic change, syn-tectonic stratigraphy related to plate movements and orogenesis.

label: time unit
definition: The time units being measured or how the numbers are expressed
examples: millions of years B.P. or thousands of years B.C.

label: top surface
definition: Container for details of top surface of a layer or stratum and it relationship with overlying layers

label: top surface feature
definition: Text description of features
examples: top surface is a hardground or rockground

label: total core recovery
definition: What percentage of the drilled material was recovered?

label: total depth
definition: The total depth in metres that was bored or dug

label: total length of section
definition: The length of the named section in meters

label: total thickness measured
definition: The total thickness of strata or rock exposed in the section or borehole

label: twinning
definition: Free text to describe any twinning features dispalyed by a mineral unit. Types include interpenetrant, rotation and geniculate.

label: type of bit
definition: What type bit was used in the drilling / cutting process - can include diameter and type code

label: unit of measurement
definition: The scale used for measurements in the analysis
examples: % for amounts or RI for refractive index.

label: unit size
definition: Free text fiekd for describing the overall size of the specimen - frequently used information and therefore placed here as a summary. Details should be entered under MeasurementOrFact complex type.

label: unit stratigraphic determination
definition: Formal stratigraphic date or correlation for an individual earth science unit (
examples: a single fossil specimen). Use efgGathering for site-related stratigraphy. This allows for individual specimens to be given an exact stratigraphic date and the wider stratigraphy of the site to also be listed.

label: unit weight
definition: Free text field to enter gross weight of geological specimens.  -  frequently used information and used here as a summary. Details should be entered under MeasurementOrFact complex type

label: upper value
definition: Higher value or upper limit of range of values

label: varietal name string
definition: Name given to a variety of the mineral, usually based on its colour or form
examples: Saphire is a blue form of Corundum, Moss Agate and Carnelian are varieties of cryptocrystalline Quartz. Marston Marble is a varietal trade name for a biomicrite from Lower Jurassic. Includes attribute for language.

label: zonal fossil type
definition: What sort of biozone is being recorded?
examples: what animal or plant group is it based on? (ammonite, brachiopod,coral, plant, foram, nanoplankton etc.)
